<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-16T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="128" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d128">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/506: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-16T17:00:00-05:00">October
                                    16, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>303. Your 520, October 16, noon.<note n="77" xml:id="d128fn77">Not
                                printed.</note> Following from Navy:</p>
                        <p>Sentence beginning “we see the logic”<note n="78" xml:id="d128fn78">Department’s telegram No. 300, October 14, 6 p.m., paragraph 7, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> refers to paragraph 4 of your
                                485<note n="79" xml:id="d128fn79">October 1, 5 p.m., <ref target="#pg_120">p. 120</ref>.</note> beginning “Regarding
                            destroyers”. We indicate in the sentence referred to that we will
                            consider any proposal British may make to end difficulty in which they
                            find themselves in respect to qualitative limitations of destroyers,
                            suggesting in the same sentence a general method of solution by transfer
                            between destroyer and cruiser (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) categories.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>